members.name: VideoPlaybackQuality.creationTime
members.description: A DOMHighResTimeStamp containing the time in miliseconds since the start of the navigation and the creation of the object.

members.name: VideoPlaybackQuality.totalVideoFrames
members.description: An unsigned long giving the number of video frames created and dropped since the creation of the associated HTMLVideoElement.

members.name: VideoPlaybackQuality.droppedVideoFrames
members.description: An unsigned long giving the number of video frames dropped since the creation of the associated HTMLVideoElement.

members.name: VideoPlaybackQuality.corruptedVideoFrames
members.description: An unsigned long giving the number of video frames corrupted since the creation of the associated HTMLVideoElement. A corrupted frame may be created or dropped.

members.name: VideoPlaybackQuality.totalFrameDelay
members.description: A double containing the sum of the frame delay since the creation of the associated HTMLVideoElement. The frame delay is the difference between a frame's theoretical presentation time and its effective display time.
